race.comment: RUMBLE TOWN (9) hadn't shown much coming into this campaign but turned in an eye-catching first-up run at Kyneton when he flashed home from last at the 250m to only be beaten 1.75 lengths. Probably goes back again from the wide gate but should be able to wind up earlier and might get over the top of them. TOWER BRIDGE (10) cost $1.3m at the sales and had trialled nicely ahead of the debut when he raced between horses for much of the race but wasn't beaten all that far. Should be better for that experience and hopefully gets a little more room. ABBY'S CROSSWORD (11) has had her fair share of opportunities but the past two runs have been among the best of her career and she has a fitness edge on some key rivals. TROOPER (1) has performed well in recent jumpouts without being extended, so he might have come on from the debut prep. PROSE AND PASTRY (13) draws well for the debut and has blinkers on, which signals intent.
